<subsection xml:id="subsec-ellipse-centered-at-hk">
   <title>Standard Forms of an Equation of an Ellipse Centered at <m>(h, k)</m></title>
  
  <p>
    Ellipses not centered at the origin are horizontal or vertical shifts of the standard form the ellipse centered at <m>(0, 0)</m>, created by replacing <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> with <m>x - h</m> and <m>y - k</m> to move the center to <m>(h, k)</m>.
  </p>

  <p>Assume: <m>a > b > 0</m>. Note: length of the major axis is <m>2a</m>, and length of the minor axis is <m>2b</m>.</p>
    <tabular bottom="minor" top="minor" left="minor" right="minor">
        <col width="25%" />
        <col width="37.5%" />
        <col width="37.5%" />
        
        <row header="yes">
            <cell><p><alert>Major Axis</alert></p></cell>
            <cell><p><alert>Horizontal</alert></p></cell>
            <cell><p><alert>Vertical</alert></p></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><p>Standard Equation</p></cell>
            <cell><p><m>\frac{(x-h)^2}{a^2} + \frac{(y-k)^2}{b^2} = 1</m></p></cell>
            <cell><p><m>\frac{(x-h)^2}{b^2} + \frac{(y-k)^2}{a^2} = 1</m></p></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><p>Vertices</p></cell>
            <cell><p><m>(h \pm a, k)</m></p></cell>
            <cell><p><m>(h, k \pm a)</m></p></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><p>Minor Axis Endpoints</p></cell>
            <cell><p><m>(h, k \pm b)</m></p></cell>
            <cell><p><m>(h \pm b, k)</m></p></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><p>Foci</p></cell>
            <cell>
                <p><m>(h \pm c, k)</m></p>
                <p><m>b^2 = a^2 - c^2</m></p>
            </cell>
            <cell>
                <p><m>(h, k \pm c)</m></p>
                <p><m>b^2 = a^2 - c^2</m></p>
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell><p>Graph</p></cell>
            <cell>
                <image source="graphics/horizontal-ellipse-1.png" width="100%" />
            </cell>
            <cell>
                <image source="graphics/vertical-ellipse-1.png" width="100%" />
            </cell>
        </row>
    </tabular>
</subsection>
<!-- Example -->
<example xml:id="ex-graph-ellipse-hk">
  <statement>
    <p>
      Graph the ellipse. Identify the center, foci, and endpoints of the minor axis.
      <me>\frac{(x+2)^2}{16} + \frac{(y-3)^2}{9} = 1</me>
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            The equation is in the form <m>\frac{(x-h)^2}{a^2} + \frac{(y-k)^2}{b^2} = 1</m>.
            Since <m>a^2 = 16</m> is larger than <m>b^2 = 9</m>, the major axis is horizontal.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            The center is <m>(h, k) = (-2, 3)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            With <m>a = 4</m> and <m>b = 3</m>, we find <m>c</m> using <m>c^2 = a^2 - b^2</m>:
            <me>c^2 = 16 - 9 = 7 \implies c = \sqrt{7}</me>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            The foci are <m>(h \pm c, k) = (-2 \pm \sqrt{7}, 3)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            The endpoints of the minor axis are <m>(h, k \pm b) = (-2, 3 \pm 3)</m>, which are <m>(-2, 6)</m> and <m>(-2, 0)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
    
    <sidebyside width="60%">
      <image xml:id="img-ellipse-example-grid">
        <description>Graph of the ellipse centered at (-2,3) with a=4 and b=3.</description>
        <latex-image>
          \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.5]
            \draw[thin, gray!40] (-7,-1) grid (3,7);
            \draw[-&gt;] (-7.2,0) -- (3.2,0) node[right] {\scriptsize $x$};
            \draw[-&gt;] (0,-1.2) -- (0,7.2) node[above] {\scriptsize $y$};
            \foreach \x in {-6,-4,-2,2} \draw (\x,2pt) -- (\x,-2pt) node[below] {\tiny $\x$};
            \foreach \y in {2,4,6} \draw (2pt,\y) -- (-2pt,\y) node[left] {\tiny $\y$};
            
            \draw[blue, thick] (-2,3) ellipse (4 and 3);
            \filldraw[red] (-2,3) circle (3pt) node[above right, black] {\tiny $(-2,3)$};
            \filldraw[red] ({ -2 + sqrt(7) }, 3) circle (2pt);
            \filldraw[red] ({ -2 - sqrt(7) }, 3) circle (2pt);
            \filldraw[blue] (-2,6) circle (2.5pt);
            \filldraw[blue] (-2,0) circle (2.5pt);
          \end{tikzpicture}
        </latex-image>
      </image>
    </sidebyside>
  </solution>
</example>
