  <example xml:id="ex-ellipse-find-equation">
  <statement>
    <p>
      Give the equation of an ellipse in standard form with center <m>(1, 3)</m>, focus at <m>(-2, 3)</m>, and vertex at <m>(5, 3)</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            The center is given as <m>(h, k) = (1, 3)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Since the center, focus, and vertex all lie on the horizontal line <m>y = 3</m>, the major axis is horizontal. The standard form is:
            <me>\frac{(x-h)^2}{a^2} + \frac{(y-k)^2}{b^2} = 1</me>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            The distance from the center <m>(1, 3)</m> to the vertex <m>(5, 3)</m> is <m>a = 5 - 1 = 4</m>, so <m>a^2 = 16</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            The distance from the center <m>(1, 3)</m> to the focus <m>(-2, 3)</m> is <m>c = 1 - (-2) = 3</m>, so <m>c^2 = 9</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Using the relationship <m>c^2 = a^2 - b^2</m>, we find <m>b^2</m>:
            <me>9 = 16 - b^2 \implies b^2 = 7</me>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Substituting the values into the standard form, we get:
            <me>\frac{(x - 1)^2}{16} + \frac{(y - 3)^2}{7} = 1</me>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </solution>
</example>
